Four suspected cases of anthrax in cattle near Lunéville
--------------------------------------------------------
The cattle died on a farm in the municipality of Hoéville in Lunévillois [Alsace-Champagne-Ardenne-Lorraine region] between Saturday night and Monday [13-15 Aug 2016]. The farmer and his neighbours are complaining that it took very long to take the samples and send them to the lab (only on Wednesday, 17 Aug 2016) and that the renderers didn't collect the carcasses immediately. They collected them yesterday, Friday [19 Aug 2016]!

Samples have been sent to the reference laboratory at Maison-Alfort and the results should be available sometime next week. The farm is under restrictions as is the usual surveillance and quarantine procedure when anthrax is suspected.

The event in the Moselle area has started earlier this month [August 2016].

