[Profound thanks to Sabine for her translation.

When dealing with anthrax outbreaks, samples must be taken promptly, not least because the full response can depend on what the laboratories find and report. When you suspect anthrax, immediately treat any suspect incubating animals with long-acting antibiotics, and the rest vaccinate; any antibiotic treated stock should be vaccinated some 10 days later. And get those carcasses burnt or removed also quickly. The longer they lie around, the more severe is any soil contamination and this ensures outbreak revisits. This farm's neighbours were complaining about the stink from these 4 carcasses. Not good enough! - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4430388,34152.]
